The paper discusses the use of LSTMs for processing unordered instance sets, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of representation learning. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on image datasets (MNIST, Lookbook, and Histopathology), which suggests that the paper could be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of weakly supervised learning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
